s3560: Thirty-ninth year: Mu Gong passed away. Buried with human sacrifices; 170 people followed in death. The noblemen criticized it, therefore do not say 'died'.
s3575: Jin Ling Gong Yi Gao's first year: Zhao Dun monopolized government.
s3578: Seventeenth year: Gong Sun Gu killed Cheng Gong.
s3588: Thirty-third year: Xiang Wang passed away.
s3589: Eighth year: the king sent Wei to request gold for burial; was discourteous.
s3591: Second year: Qin attacked us, took Wu Cheng, to avenge the battle of Ling Qiu.
s3594: Song Zhao Gong Chu Jiu's first year: son of Xiang Gong.
s3607: Third year: led the feudal lords to rescue Zheng.
s3609: Eighth year: attacked Zheng because they submitted to Jin.
s3623: Fourth year: attacked Qin, captured Shao Liang. Qin took our Bei Zheng.
s3624: Fourth year: Jin attacked us, took Shao Liang. We attacked Jin and took Bei Zheng.
s3637: Eleventh year: defeated the Chang Di at Xian and returned, captured the Chang Di.
s3642: Fourth year: defeated the Chang Di at Chang Qiu.
s3655: Sixth year: Qin took our Ji Ma. Fought with Qin at He Qu, Qin army retreated.
s3656: Sixth year: attacked Jin, took Ji Ma. Angry, fought a great battle with us at He Qu.
s3672: Seventh year: Jin deceitfully obtained Sui Hui.
s3684: Sixth year: Qing Wang passed away. The nobles contended for government, therefore no announcement was made.
s3696: Eighteenth year: the Rong attacked us; defeated them at Jin.
